e repeated mention of the sperm-drop [nutfah] in the Mighty Book is not merely to hear its word and abandon reflection upon its meaning. So look now at the sperm-drop: it is a droplet of water, foul; if left for an hour for the air to strike it, it would spoil and become putrid. How did the Lord of Lords bring it forth from the loins and the ribs? And how did He bring together the male and the female, and cast affection [ulfah] and love [mahabbah] into their hearts [qulūb]? And how did He lead them by the chain of love and desire to union? And how did He extract the sperm-drop from the man through the movement of intercourse? And how did He draw the menstrual blood from the depths of the veins and gather it in the womb?\n\nThen, how did He create the infant from the sperm-drop, and nourish it with the water of menstruation, and feed it until it grew, increased, and became large? And how did He make the sperm-drop, which is white and shining, into a clinging clot ['alaqah] that is red? Then how did He make it a chewed lump [mudghah]? Then how did He divide the parts of the sperm-drop, which are equal and similar, into bones, nerves, veins, tendons, and flesh? Then how did He construct from the flesh, nerves, and veins the outward limbs: the roundness of the head, the aperture of hearing, sight, the nose, the mouth, and the rest of the openings? Then He extended the hand and the foot, and divided their ends into fingers, and divided the fingers into fingertips?\n\nThen how did He construct the inward organs: the heart [qalb], the stomach, the liver, the spleen, the lung, the womb, the bladder, and the intestines—each one with a specific form, a specific measure, for a specific function? Then how did He divide each of these organs into other divisions? He constructed the eye from seven layers; for each layer a specific attribute and a specific configuration—if a single layer from them were lost, or an attribute from its attributes were removed, the eye would be incapacitated from sight.\n\nSo look now at the bones: they are solid, strong bodies. How did He create them from a weak, delicate sperm-drop? Then He made them the framework [qiwām] for the body and its support. Then He proportioned them with different measures and different forms: among them small and large, long and round, hollow and solid, broad and slender.</div></div></div>"}},"21":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.45","c":"فَجَعَلْنَاهُ","d":"fajaʿalnāhu","e":"ُhَٰnْlَʿعَjgَf"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.76","c":"فِي","d":"fī","e":"àِf"},{"b":"1.6","h":"3.54","c":"قَرَارٍ","d":"qarārin","e":"ٍrāَrَq"},{"b":"3.4","h":"5.94","c":"مَكِينٍ","d":"makīnin","e":"ٍnyِkَّm"}],"a":{"g":"And We placed it in a firm lodging"}},"22":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.25","c":"إِلَى","d":"ilā","e":"ٰàَlِiʾ"},{"b":"0.48","h":"1.04","c":"قَدَرٍ","d":"qadarin","e":"ٍrَdَq"},{"b":"2.0","h":"2.87","c":"مَعْلُومٍ","d":"maʿlūmin","e":"ٍmwُlْʿعَّm"}],"a":{"g":"For a known extent."}},"23":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.4","c":"فَقَدَرْنَا","d":"faqadarnā","e":"āَnْrَdَqَf"},{"b":"1.0","h":"2.24","c":"فَنِعْمَ","d":"faniʿ'ma","e":"َmْʿعِnَf"},{"b":"1.8","h":"3.77","c":"الْقَادِرُونَ","d":"l-qādirūna","e":"َnwُrِdَٰqْlٱ"}],"a":{"g":"And We determined [it], and excellent [are We] to determine."}},"24":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"وَيْلٌ","d":"waylun","e":"ٌlْyَw"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.27","c":"يَوْمَئِذٍ","d":"yawma-idhin","e":"ٍhdِyʾَmْwَy"},{"b":"2.5","h":"4.31","c":"لِلْمُكَذِّبِينَ","d":"lil'mukadhibīna","e":"َnyِbِّhdَkُmْlِّl"}],"a":{"g":"Woe, that Day, to the deniers."}},"25":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.75","c":"أَلَمْ","d":"alam","e":"ْmَlَaʾ"},{"b":"0.49","h":"1.38","c":"نَجْعَلِ","d":"najʿali","e":"ِlَʿعْjgَn"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.7","c":"الْأَرْضَ","d":"l-arḍa","e":"َḍْrَaʾْlٱ"},{"b":"1.9","h":"3.96","c":"كِفَاتًا","d":"kifātan","e":"āًtāَfِk"}],"a":{"g":"Have We not made the earth a container","ihya":"<div class='ihya-container' style='margin-top: 20px; padding: 15px; background-color: #f8f9fa; border-left: 4px solid #d4af37; border-radius: 4px;'><h4 style='color: #d4af37; margin-bottom: 15px; font-family: \"Cinzel\", serif;'>Ihya 'Ulum al-Din Commentary</h4><div class='ihya-entry'><span class='badge badge-light' style='color: #666; border: 1px solid #ddd; margin-bottom: 8px;'>j4 k09</span><div class='ihya-text' style='font-size: 1.1em; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;'>Indeed, its surface [zahiruha] is a dwelling place [maqarr] for the living [al-ahya'], and its interior [batnuha] is a resting place [marqad] for the dead [al-amwat]. The Most High has said: \"Have We not made the earth a receptacle [kifatan], for the living and the dead?\"</div></div></div>"}},"26":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.45","c":"أَحْيَاءً","d":"aḥyāan","e":"ًءٓāَyْḥَaʾ"},{"b":"0.91","h":"3.5","c":"وَأَمْوَاتًا","d":"wa-amwātan","e":"āًtَٰwْmَaʾَw"}],"a":{"g":"Of the living and the dead?"}},"27":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.46","c":"وَجَعَلْنَا","d":"wajaʿalnā","e":"āَnْlَʿعَjgَw"},{"b":"1.1","h":"2.38","c":"فِيهَا","d":"fīhā","e":"āَhyِf"},{"b":"1.8","h":"3.93","c":"رَوَاسِيَ","d":"rawāsiya","e":"َàِsَٰwَr"},{"b":"2.8","h":"5.81","c":"شَامِخَاتٍ","d":"shāmikhātin","e":"ٍtَٰhkِmَٰhs"},{"b":"4.3","h":"8.89","c":"وَأَسْقَيْنَاكُمْ","d":"wa-asqaynākum","e":"mُkَٰnْyَqْsَaʾَw"},{"b":"7.1","h":"12.64","c":"مَاءً","d":"māan","e":"ًءٓāَّm"},{"b":"9.7","h":"15.31","c":"فُرَاتًا","d":"furātan","e":"āًtāَrُf"}],"a":{"g":"And We placed therein lofty, firmly set mountains and have given you to drink sweet water."}},"28":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.45","c":"وَيْلٌ","d":"waylun","e":"ٌlْyَw"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.15","c":"يَوْمَئِذٍ","d":"yawma-idhin","e":"ٍhdِyʾَmْwَy"},{"b":"2.4","h":"4.57","c":"لِلْمُكَذِّبِينَ","d":"lil'mukadhibīna","e":"َnyِbِّhdَkُmْlِّl"}],"a":{"g":"Woe, that Day, to the deniers."}},"29":{"w":[{"b":"0.27","h":"0.35","c":"انْطَلِقُوا","d":"inṭaliqū","e":"۟āٓwُqِlَṭnٱ"},{"b":"3.7","h":"4.14","c":"إِلَى","d":"ilā","e":"ٰàَlِiʾ"},{"b":"4.3","h":"5.12","c":"مَا","d":"mā","e":"āَm"},{"b":"4.6","h":"5.83","c":"كُنْتُمْ